[32m│[0m ## detailed_summary                                                                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Performed systematic XSS payload testing on `http://127.0.0.1:33031/page` endpoint with 15 payloads targeting the `solution`      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parameter. Results indicate **strong input filtering/sanitization** is in place for most XSS vectors, with only `<script>` tags   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m making it through to the JavaScript execution layer.                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Key Findings:                                                                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **1. Alert Triggered but Wrong Value:**                                                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Payload:** `<script>alert('XSS')</script>`                                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Result:** Alert executed but returned error: `TypeError: Attempting to change the setter of an unconfigurable property.`      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m instead of "XSS"                                                                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **2. Blocked/Filtered Payloads (14 total):**                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m All event-handler-based payloads were completely blocked:                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<svg onload=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=window.alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=self.alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=top.alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=parent.alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=eval(alert('XSS'))>` - BLOCKED                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img src=x onerror=eval('alert(\'XSS\')')>` - BLOCKED                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<img/src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<body onload=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<iframe onload=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<input onfocus=alert('XSS') autofocus>` - BLOCKED                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<video><source onerror=alert('XSS')></video>` - BLOCKED                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `<details open ontoggle=alert('XSS')>` - BLOCKED                                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **3. Error Message for Blocked Payloads:**                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m No explicit error messages were shown for blocked payloads. All 14 blocked payloads returned HTTP 200 with the normal HTML page   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m structure.                                                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **4. Behavioral Differences:**                                                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Different alert paths (window.alert, self.alert, top.alert, parent.alert)**: All FAILED equally - blocked at input level      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m before reaching JavaScript context                                                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Script vs Event handlers**: Only `<script>` tags bypass input filter but still fail at execution due to prototype pollution   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m protection                                                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Variable alert values**: Unable to test - all event handler alerts blocked before execution                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Conclusion:**                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application has **two layers of protection**:                                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Input sanitizer/WAF**: Blocks HTML tags with event handlers (`onerror`, `onload`, etc.) and SVG tags entirely                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Prototype pollution protection**: Blocks direct `alert()` calls within `<script>` tags                                       [32m│[0m
