[32m│[0m ## thoughts                                                                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The results reveal a sophisticated defense-in-depth approach. The application is using:                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Input filtering layer**: Sanitizes HTML event handlers and dangerous tags. The fact that all 14 event-handler payloads       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m failed while `<script>` passed through suggests regex-based filtering targeting `on*` attributes.                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **JavaScript runtime protection**: The `<script>` tag execution was intercepted with a TypeError about "changing setter of     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m unconfigurable property" - this is characteristic of prototype pollution defenses that seal/freeze `Object.prototype`.            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Why the different alert paths failed:**                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `window.alert`, `self.alert`, `top.alert`, and `parent.alert` all point to the same underlying `alert` function in the global     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m scope. The application isn't blocking different references - it's blocking the entire input containing `onerror=` patterns before [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m they even reach the browser.                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
