[2;36m│[0m Based on my testing, I've discovered something interesting:                            [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. **Any JSON Content-Type request bypasses the alert detection** - even an empty JSON [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m object `{}` returns "Let the game begin. Good Luck" instead of the error               [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. **Form data with constructor/proto pollution also bypasses** when sent directly     [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m without the `solution` parameter                                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 3. **The server only triggers the error detection when the payload is sent as          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m URL-encoded form data with the `solution` parameter**                                  [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m This suggests the protection mechanism only looks at the URL-encoded `solution`        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m parameter value, not JSON bodies or other form fields.                                 [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m However, the task was specifically to test **prototype pollution** to disable/override [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m alert() protection. The payloads I tried that changed the response didn't actually     [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m demonstrate prototype pollution working to disable protection - they just bypassed     [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m CONTENT-TYPE filtering or parameter name filtering.                                    [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m Let me try a more strategic approach:                                                  [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. First pollute via JSON/proto payload                                                [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. Then send an alert to see if protection is disabled                                 [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
