[32m│[0m - Always returns: Static landing page with "Dalgona Challenges" heading                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Query parameters are completely ignored                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Conclusion                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **No GET-based XSS vulnerabilities exist**. The only reflection point is:              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **POST /page** with `solution=<value>` (body parameter)                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - This requires form submission, not query string manipulation                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application only processes `solution` from POST body form data. GET query          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parameters are not processed for reflection on any endpoint.                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Tested 6 GET query parameter combinations across 2 endpoints (`/page` and `/`) with    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m both specific query parameters (`solution`, `payload`) and a generic probe (`test`).   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m None of the GET requests reflected the query parameter values in the response body.    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The `/page` endpoint on GET always returns a static form HTML with the message "Let    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the game begin. Good Luck" regardless of query parameters. The `/` endpoint on GET     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m always returns the landing page "Dalgona Challenges" page with no query parameter      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m processing. The only reflection point remains POST `/page` with the `solution` body    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parameter. Since GET parameters don't reflect, the attack surface is limited to POST   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m body submissions which have known filtering mechanisms (blocks "alert" substring and   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m event handlers).                                                                       [32m│[0m
